spanGrp.span: ‘I saw that the frog, the coati and the dog were running;
Í sũã'-je-nã buke ã sirak jemẽ chichi je tur-gẽ
the phone was ringing, the dog picked it up and spoke with his wife.
(_) (_) telefono tsei blar-gẽ Je gugá-ite-ra í ktö'-gẽ rö juape ra (m) (_)
The dog’s wife was the coati;
Ñẽ chichi juape juela rö sirak
It seems that they listened to each other and agreed on going to fuck around.
í juela-nã (_) jebi í ñã kein-sã' í í ñã kablá ñã wable-nã
It seems that they went; the dog drove the car to the coati’s;
Í juela kepi í mẽnẽũ-mĩ í tebeli_yaga sigá-sã'-ite mẽnẽũ juape jũga
he picked her up and took her far away; he crossed the mountain and went down;
Í juape jiá-ite (_) tebeli_yaga nã í mẽnẽ' í wã komĩ' kabata ká-ite kabata diékke kabata tsabataka
they got to a plane place.
Í degãũ (_) kã' kẽi blali ska
A frog and a big snake passed by and it seems that they stopped the car,
(_) Buke jamẽ kebé tã'ĩ káũ (_) juela bi je të í í tebeli_yaga wöketsĩwã-ite
the car turned over and the dog died.
ñerö í të (m) í tebeli_yaga buganã' junã-mĩ jie-wa të kã'kbá Ñẽ chichi döá-wã
The frog rushed to see him and cried a lot by its side and in front of him.
buke tunã'u-mĩ í sũã' Je jiñã' köũ í sepe mẽ í wömĩ
The coati was hanging from a branch;
Í ksela kepi sirak kel kichake-lë í mẽlẽk wa kaljula jãrga
he did not hesitate to jump down;
Je të ka í të í begetse-gẽ jẽk (_) báu-mĩ
it is incredible but his spirit went out
kayue juela bi í jueiglö desãũ-te ñerö
siga-wa të gugá je kĩ' ñãtuá (_) í wagi nã
and put in back into his body and him to the sorcerers
Jebi í pakká-ite böi-wã-nã jawá-wa wö
Then they saw him again; he was broken;
Je kepi juela tögapa í kwã'-ite-ra pã'-lë-wã
[the frog] looked for a bed in the bush and cured him with remedies;
Kã'kshã' jãrga í jaka yulá-ite ĩã jeska í böiwã'-ite pepli wa
he rubbed his ass and it seems that he enjoyed it [because] he closed his eyes at that point.
Í ñãkyaka pasige-gẽ-ite kepa í juela bi í kei kse-gẽ-ite bá je wöbla wötiö-gẽ je_jueta
He cured him and drove him to their place by the same road they came;
Í böiwã'-wã-ite í tebeli_yaga inga í katse-mĩ í (_) wã í (m) wakwa jũga Mãĩ í dé wã
the coati fixed the car and they went back.’
sirak të tebeli_yaga böiwã' bá je inga í damãu-lo (_) í mẽnẽũ-lo-mĩ
